## Functions

### copy&#95;if&#95;else() {#abd1fd06683a32de0138c4ba80b0836b4}

<MemberDefinition
  template={<>template &lt;class InputIt, class OutputIt1, class OutputIt2, class UnaryPredicate&gt;</>}
  prototype={<>static std::pair&lt; OutputIt1, OutputIt2 &gt; copy&#95;if&#95;else (InputIt First, InputIt Last, OutputIt1 d1, OutputIt2 d2, UnaryPredicate Predicate)</>}
  labels = {["static"]}>
Copy elements in the range &#91;First, Last) to d1 when the predicate is true or d2 when the predicate is false.

This is essentially both std::copy&#95;if and std::remove&#95;copy&#95;if combined into a single pass.

Definition at line <a href="#l00072">72</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/mips/lib/target/mips/mctargetdesc/mipselfobjectwriter-cpp">MipsELFObjectWriter.cpp</a>.
</MemberDefinition>

### find&#95;best() {#a268abe30400a55226d690105cc187f01}

<MemberDefinition
  template={<>template &lt;class InputIt, class UnaryPredicate, class Comparator&gt;</>}
  prototype={<>static InputIt find&#95;best (InputIt First, InputIt Last, UnaryPredicate Predicate, Comparator BetterThan)</>}
  labels = {["static"]}>
Find the best match in the range &#91;First, Last).

An element matches when <a href="/docs/api/classes/predicate">Predicate(X)</a> returns FindBest&#95;Match or FindBest&#95;PerfectMatch. A value of FindBest&#95;PerfectMatch also terminates the search. BetterThan(A, B) is a comparator that returns true when A is a better match than B. The return value is the position of the best match.

This is similar to std::find&#95;if but finds the best of multiple possible matches.

Definition at line <a href="#l00098">98</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/mips/lib/target/mips/mctargetdesc/mipselfobjectwriter-cpp">MipsELFObjectWriter.cpp</a>.
</MemberDefinition>

### getMatchingLoType() {#af29f17b9965a9f3bdcbbfafbf90b7f0c}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>static unsigned getMatchingLoType (<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64promoteconstant-cpp/#a90f8350fecae261c25be85d38b451bff">const</a> <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/elfrelocationentry">ELFRelocationEntry</a> &amp; Reloc)</>}
  labels = {["static"]}>
Determine the low relocation that matches the given relocation.

If the relocation does not need a low relocation then the return value is ELF::R&#95;MIPS&#95;NONE.

The relocations that need a matching low part are R&#95;(MIPS|MICROMIPS|MIPS16)&#95;HI16 for all symbols and R&#95;(MIPS|MICROMIPS|MIPS16)&#95;GOT16 for local symbols only.

Definition at line <a href="#l00122">122</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/mips/lib/target/mips/mctargetdesc/mipselfobjectwriter-cpp">MipsELFObjectWriter.cpp</a>.
</MemberDefinition>

<Link id="l00334" /><CodeLine lineNumber="334"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Sort relocation table entries by offset except where another order is</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00335" /><CodeLine lineNumber="335"><Highlight kind="comment">/// required by the MIPS ABI.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00336" /><CodeLine lineNumber="336"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00337" /><CodeLine lineNumber="337"><Highlight kind="comment">/// MIPS has a few relocations that have an AHL component in the expression used</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00338" /><CodeLine lineNumber="338"><Highlight kind="comment">/// to evaluate them. This AHL component is an addend with the same number of</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00339" /><CodeLine lineNumber="339"><Highlight kind="comment">/// bits as a symbol value but not all of our ABI&#39;s are able to supply a</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00340" /><CodeLine lineNumber="340"><Highlight kind="comment">/// sufficiently sized addend in a single relocation.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00341" /><CodeLine lineNumber="341"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00342" /><CodeLine lineNumber="342"><Highlight kind="comment">/// The O32 ABI for example, uses REL relocations which store the addend in the</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00343" /><CodeLine lineNumber="343"><Highlight kind="comment">/// section data. All the relocations with AHL components affect 16-bit fields</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00344" /><CodeLine lineNumber="344"><Highlight kind="comment">/// so the addend for a single relocation is limited to 16-bit. This ABI</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00345" /><CodeLine lineNumber="345"><Highlight kind="comment">/// resolves the limitation by linking relocations (e.g. R&#95;MIPS&#95;HI16 and</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00346" /><CodeLine lineNumber="346"><Highlight kind="comment">/// R&#95;MIPS&#95;LO16) and distributing the addend between the linked relocations. The</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00347" /><CodeLine lineNumber="347"><Highlight kind="comment">/// ABI mandates that such relocations must be next to each other in a</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00348" /><CodeLine lineNumber="348"><Highlight kind="comment">/// particular order (e.g. R&#95;MIPS&#95;HI16 must be immediately followed by a</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00349" /><CodeLine lineNumber="349"><Highlight kind="comment">/// matching R&#95;MIPS&#95;LO16) but the rule is less strict in practice.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00350" /><CodeLine lineNumber="350"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00351" /><CodeLine lineNumber="351"><Highlight kind="comment">/// The de facto standard is lenient in the following ways:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00352" /><CodeLine lineNumber="352"><Highlight kind="comment">/// - &#39;Immediately following&#39; does not refer to the next relocation entry but</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00353" /><CodeLine lineNumber="353"><Highlight kind="comment">///   the next matching relocation.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00354" /><CodeLine lineNumber="354"><Highlight kind="comment">/// - There may be multiple high parts relocations for one low part relocation.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00355" /><CodeLine lineNumber="355"><Highlight kind="comment">/// - There may be multiple low part relocations for one high part relocation.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00356" /><CodeLine lineNumber="356"><Highlight kind="comment">/// - The AHL addend in each part does not have to be exactly equal as long as</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00357" /><CodeLine lineNumber="357"><Highlight kind="comment">///   the difference does not affect the carry bit from bit 15 into 16 This is</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00358" /><CodeLine lineNumber="358"><Highlight kind="comment">///   to allow, for example, the use of %lo(foo) and %lo(foo+4) when loading</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00359" /><CodeLine lineNumber="359"><Highlight kind="comment">///   both halves of a long long.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00360" /><CodeLine lineNumber="360"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00361" /><CodeLine lineNumber="361"><Highlight kind="comment">/// See getMatchingLoType() for a description of which high part relocations</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00362" /><CodeLine lineNumber="362"><Highlight kind="comment">/// match which low part relocations. One particular thing to note is that</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00363" /><CodeLine lineNumber="363"><Highlight kind="comment">/// R&#95;MIPS&#95;GOT16 and similar only have AHL addends if they refer to local</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00364" /><CodeLine lineNumber="364"><Highlight kind="comment">/// symbols.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00365" /><CodeLine lineNumber="365"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00366" /><CodeLine lineNumber="366"><Highlight kind="comment">/// It should also be noted that this function is not affected by whether</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00367" /><CodeLine lineNumber="367"><Highlight kind="comment">/// the symbol was kept or rewritten into a section-relative equivalent. We</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00368" /><CodeLine lineNumber="368"><Highlight kind="comment">/// always match using the expressions from the source.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00369" /><CodeLine lineNumber="369" lineLink="/docs/api/classes/anonymous-namespace-mipselfobjectwriter-cpp-/mipselfobjectwriter/#a5fb8605e7260a242de5a25e2b3add57d"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordtype">void</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> <a href="/docs/api/classes/anonymous-namespace-mipselfobjectwriter-cpp-/mipselfobjectwriter/#a5fb8605e7260a242de5a25e2b3add57d">MipsELFObjectWriter::sortRelocs</a>(</Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">const</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/mcassembler">MCAssembler</a> &amp;Asm,</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00370" /><CodeLine lineNumber="370"><Highlight kind="normal">                                     std::vector&lt;ELFRelocationEntry&gt; &amp;Relocs) &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00371" /><CodeLine lineNumber="371"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// We do not need to sort the relocation table for RELA relocations which</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00372" /><CodeLine lineNumber="372"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// N32/N64 uses as the relocation addend contains the value we require,</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00373" /><CodeLine lineNumber="373"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// rather than it being split across a pair of relocations.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00374" /><CodeLine lineNumber="374"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">if</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/mcelfobjecttargetwriter/#a18895a2343e1b4a90083d13c8ddc90cd">hasRelocationAddend</a>())</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00375" /><CodeLine lineNumber="375"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">return</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal">;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00376" /><CodeLine lineNumber="376"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00377" /><CodeLine lineNumber="377"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// Sort relocations by the address they are applied to.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00378" /><CodeLine lineNumber="378"><Highlight kind="normal">  <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#a74cdbd1e4f731e7d7cd83461b8b1de0b">llvm::sort</a>(Relocs,</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00379" /><CodeLine lineNumber="379"><Highlight kind="normal">             &#91;&#93;(</Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">const</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/elfrelocationentry">ELFRelocationEntry</a> &amp;<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/ir/builtingcs-cpp/#a2e38c85003a042421cde1647632d0b72">A</a>, </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">const</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/elfrelocationentry">ELFRelocationEntry</a> &amp;<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/ir/builtingcs-cpp/#ae76959fe811ba090de4cba69ac00f1da">B</a>) &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00380" /><CodeLine lineNumber="380"><Highlight kind="normal">               </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">return</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/ir/builtingcs-cpp/#a2e38c85003a042421cde1647632d0b72">A</a>.Offset &lt; <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/ir/builtingcs-cpp/#ae76959fe811ba090de4cba69ac00f1da">B</a>.Offset;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00381" /><CodeLine lineNumber="381"><Highlight kind="normal">             &#125;);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00382" /><CodeLine lineNumber="382"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00383" /><CodeLine lineNumber="383"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// Place relocations in a list for reorder convenience. Hi16 contains the</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00384" /><CodeLine lineNumber="384"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// iterators of high-part relocations.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00385" /><CodeLine lineNumber="385"><Highlight kind="normal">  std::list&lt;MipsRelocationEntry&gt; Sorted;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00386" /><CodeLine lineNumber="386"><Highlight kind="normal">  <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/smallvector">SmallVector&lt;std::list&lt;MipsRelocationEntry&gt;::iterator</a>, 0&gt; Hi16;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00387" /><CodeLine lineNumber="387"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">for</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> (</Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">auto</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> &amp;R : Relocs) &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00388" /><CodeLine lineNumber="388"><Highlight kind="normal">    Sorted.push&#95;back(R);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00389" /><CodeLine lineNumber="389"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">if</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> (<a href="#af29f17b9965a9f3bdcbbfafbf90b7f0c">getMatchingLoType</a>(R) != ELF::R&#95;MIPS&#95;NONE)</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00390" /><CodeLine lineNumber="390"><Highlight kind="normal">      Hi16.<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/smallvectortemplatebase/#af42bfbc067df27c19ee2fc859df58799">push&#95;back</a>(std::prev(Sorted.end()));</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00391" /><CodeLine lineNumber="391"><Highlight kind="normal">  &#125;</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00393" /><CodeLine lineNumber="393"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">for</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> (</Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">auto</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/support/md5-cpp/#ac0eafdc9ee161b71e7af98af736952fd">I</a> : Hi16) &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00396" /><CodeLine lineNumber="396"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// If the next relocation is a perfect match, continue;</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00397" /><CodeLine lineNumber="397"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">if</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> (std::next(<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/support/md5-cpp/#ac0eafdc9ee161b71e7af98af736952fd">I</a>) != Sorted.end() &amp;&amp;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00398" /><CodeLine lineNumber="398"><Highlight kind="normal">        <a href="#a0b9745f3db31eb4f80f4acdaff1bbe76">isMatchingReloc</a>(MatchingType, R, std::next(<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/support/md5-cpp/#ac0eafdc9ee161b71e7af98af736952fd">I</a>)-&gt;R))</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00400" /><CodeLine lineNumber="400"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// Otherwise, find the best matching low-part relocation with the following</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00401" /><CodeLine lineNumber="401"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// criteria. It must have the same symbol and its addend is no lower than</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00402" /><CodeLine lineNumber="402"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// that of the current high-part.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00403" /><CodeLine lineNumber="403"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00404" /><CodeLine lineNumber="404"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// (1) %lo with a smaller offset is preferred.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00405" /><CodeLine lineNumber="405"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// (2) %lo with the same offset that is unmatched is preferred.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00406" /><CodeLine lineNumber="406"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// (3) later %lo is preferred.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00407" /><CodeLine lineNumber="407"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">auto</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> Best = Sorted.end();</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00408" /><CodeLine lineNumber="408"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">for</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> (</Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">auto</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> J = Sorted.begin(); J != Sorted.end(); ++J) &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00409" /><CodeLine lineNumber="409"><Highlight kind="normal">      </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">auto</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> &amp;R1 = J-&gt;R;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00410" /><CodeLine lineNumber="410"><Highlight kind="normal">      </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">if</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> (R1.Type == MatchingType &amp;&amp; R.Symbol == R1.Symbol &amp;&amp;</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00412" /><CodeLine lineNumber="412"><Highlight kind="normal">          (Best == Sorted.end() || R1.Addend &lt; Best-&gt;R.Addend ||</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00413" /><CodeLine lineNumber="413"><Highlight kind="normal">           (!Best-&gt;Matched &amp;&amp; R1.Addend == Best-&gt;R.Addend)))</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00415" /><CodeLine lineNumber="415"><Highlight kind="normal">    &#125;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00416" /><CodeLine lineNumber="416"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">if</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> (Best != Sorted.end() &amp;&amp; R.Addend == Best-&gt;R.Addend)</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00419" /><CodeLine lineNumber="419"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// Move the high-part before the low-part, or if not found, the end of the</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00421" /><CodeLine lineNumber="421"><Highlight kind="normal">    Sorted.splice(Best, Sorted, <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/support/md5-cpp/#ac0eafdc9ee161b71e7af98af736952fd">I</a>);</Highlight></CodeLine>
